  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Revascularization Status</measure>
    <time_frame>Post-procedure, immediate=at the end of the procedure, per last angiogram during treatment</time_frame>
    <description>Revascularization, defined as at least TICI 2a in the vascular territory treated at end of the neuro interventional procedure Thrombolysis in Cerebral Infarction (TICI) grading system for perfusion (ie blood flow through a vessel) Grade 0:No Perfusion. No antegrade flow beyond the point of occlusion. Grade 1:Penetration With Minimal Perfusion. Grade 2:Partial Perfusion. Grade 2a:Only partial filling (&lt;2/3) of the entire vascular territory is visualized. Grade 2b:Complete filling of all of the expected vascular territory is visualized, but slower . Grade 3:Complete Perfusion.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
