  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. age (18-80 years)

          2. acute ischemic stroke

          3. within 8 hours after symptom onset

          4. a large-vessel confirmed by CTA/MRA (eg, internal carotid, middle cerebral M1 and/or
             M2 segments)

          5. NIHSS(≥8 and ≤24)

          6. patients or their legally authorised representatives provided signed, informed
             consent.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. CT or MRI evidence of intracranial haemorrhage/tumor

          2. major ischaemic infarction (acute ischaemic change in more than a third of the middle
             cerebral artery territory)

          3. NIHSS(≥25 and ≤7)

          4. severe sustained hypertension (systolic blood pressure &gt;185 mm Hg or diastolic blood
             pressure &gt;110 mm Hg)

          5. baseline glucose concentrations of less than 2·7 mmol/L or higher than 21.6 mmol/L

          6. known haemorrhagic diathesis, coagulation factor deficiency, or oral anticoagulant
             therapy with an international normalised ratio of more than 1.7

          7. treatment with heparin within 48 h with a partial thromboplastin time more than two
             times the laboratory normal, baseline platelet count of less than 100×10^9/L

          8. history of severe allergy (worse than rash) to contrast medium or nitinol

          9. pregnancy
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
